enu-item-type-taxonomy menu-item-object-category menu-item-13696\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/pizza/\">Pizza</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-6707\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-taxonomy menu-item-object-category menu-item-6707\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/salads/\">salads</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-6708\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-taxonomy menu-item-object-category menu-item-6708\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/slow-cooker/\">slow cooker</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-6709\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-taxonomy menu-item-object-category menu-item-6709\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/soup/\">soup</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-6710\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-taxonomy menu-item-object-category menu-item-6710\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/vegetables/\">vegetables</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-6704\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-taxonomy menu-item-object-category menu-item-6704\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/dessert/\">dessert</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-6705\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-taxonomy menu-item-object-category menu-item-6705\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/how-to/\">how-to</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li id=\"menu-item-17798\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-has-children menu-item-17798\"><a href=\"http://budgetbytes.ziplist.com/recipes/box\">Recipe Box</a>\n<ul class=\"sub-menu\">\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-17799\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-17799\"><a href=\"http://budgetbytes.ziplist.com/mylist\">Shopping List</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-17800\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-17800\"><a href=\"http://budgetbytes.ziplist.com/recipes/meal_planner\">Meal Planner</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-17801\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-17801\"><a href=\"http://budgetbytes.ziplist.com/deals\">Grocery Deals</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"right search\"><form method=\"get\" class=\"searchform search-form\" action=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/\" role=\"search\" ><input type=\"text\" value=\"search budget bytes\" name=\"s\" class=\"s search-input\" onfocus=\"if (&#039;search budget bytes&#039; === this.value) {this.value = &#039;&#039;;}\" onblur=\"if (&#039;&#039; === this.value) {this.value = &#039;search budget bytes&#039;;}\" /><input type=\"submit\" class=\"searchsubmit search-submit\" value=\"Search\" /></form></li></ul></div></div><div id=\"inner\"><div class=\"wrap\"><div id=\"content-sidebar-wrap\"><div id=\"content\" class=\"hfeed\"><div class=\"breadcrumb\">You are here: <a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/\" title=\"View Home\">Home</a> / <a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/\" title=\"View all items in recipes\">recipes</a> / <a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/\" title=\"View all items in misc.\">misc.</a> / <a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/bread/\" title=\"View all items in bread\">bread</a> / no-knead ciabatta</div><div class=\"post-13392 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-bread category-sandwich category-vegan category-vegetarian entry\"><div class=\"post-info\"><span class=\"date published time\" title=\"2010-12-02T18:09:00+00:00\">12.02.10</span> </div><h1 class=\"entry-title\">no-knead ciabatta</h1> \n<div class=\"recipe-cost\">$0.74 recipe / $0.12 serving</div><div class=\"entry-content\"><p>I know, man can not live on bread alone. So I&#8217;m a little obsessed with baking bread lately&#8230; humor me. There will be more &#8220;real food&#8221; soon, promise.</p>\n<p>You may remember <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YX_6l2bmvQI\">this video</a> that I referenced in my very first no-knead bread recipe post. The recipe and technique in the video are a little different from the basic no-knead recipe. The dough is wetter, it ferments for 18 hours at room temperature and is shaped into a long, fairly flat, ciabatta shaped loaf.</p>\n<p>Well, I&#8217;m glad I decided to give this one a try. For some reason it seems easier than the original no-knead and the result so much better. The inside is lighter and fluffier. The flavor is wonderful. The shape, although flat, is perfect for sandwiches. PERFECT.</p>\n<p>I followed the instructions in the <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YX_6l2bmvQI\">video</a> exactly. The <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YX_6l2bmvQI\">video</a> is great so give it a quick watch (it&#8217;s only 5 minutes long) before making the bread. The only change I&#8217;ll make next time is to divide it in two and make two smaller loafs. Everything else is just easy and perfect.</p>\n<p>This is my new go-to bread!</p>\n<h2>No-Knead Ciabatta</h2>\n<p><img alt=\"no knead ciabatta\" src=\"http://lh6.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgedQJEBQI/AAAAAAAACSk/BioUeutIG6s/s640/Ciabatta%20sliced%20buttered.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><a name=\"more\"></a></p>\n<div class=\"easyrecipe\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Recipe\">\n<link itemprop=\"image\" href=\"http://lh6.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgedQJEBQI/AAAAAAAACSk/BioUeutIG6s/s640/Ciabatta%20sliced%20buttered.jpg\"/>\n<div itemprop=\"name\" class=\"ERSName\">no-knead ciabatta</div>\n<div class=\"ERSClear\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div class=\"ERSTopRight\">\n<div class=\"ERSSavePrint\"> <span class=\"ERSSaveBtnSpan\"><script type='text/javascript' src='http://www.ziplist.com/javascripts/wk.js'></script><a class='ziplist-button add-recipe large ERSSaveBtn' href='http://www.ziplist.com/webkitchen/button/add_recipe?as_partner=budgetbytes&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.budgetbytes.com%2F2010%2F12%2Fno-knead-ciabatta%2F' target='_blank'>Save</a></span> <span class=\"ERSPrintBtnSpan\"><a class=\"ERSPrintBtn\" href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/easyrecipe-print/13392-0/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Print</a></span> </div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSTimes\">\n<div class=\"ERSTime\">\n<div class=\"ERSTimeHeading\">Prep time</div>\n<div class=\"ERSTimeItem\"> <time itemprop=\"prepTime\" datetime=\"PT10M\">10 mins</time> </div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSTime ERSTimeRight\">\n<div class=\"ERSTimeHeading\">Cook time</div>\n<div class=\"ERSTimeItem\"> <time itemprop=\"cookTime\" datetime=\"PT30M\">30 mins</time> </div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSTime ERSTimeRight\">\n<div class=\"ERSTimeHeading\">Total time</div>\n<div class=\"ERSTimeItem\"> <time itemprop=\"totalTime\" datetime=\"PT40M\">40 mins</time> </div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSClearLeft\">&nbsp;</div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"divERSHeadItems\">\n<div>Total Cost: <span itemprop=\"recipeCategory\">$0.74</span></div>\n<div>Cost Per Serving: <span itemprop=\"recipeCuisine\">$0.12</span></div>\n<div>Serves: <span itemprop=\"recipeYield\">6</span></div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSIngredients\">\n<div class=\"ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading\">Ingredients</div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 cup whole wheat flour $0.16</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">3 cups bread flour $0.44</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac14; tsp instant yeast $0.02</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">1&frac12; tsp salt $0.05</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">2 cups warm water $0.00</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 Tbsp vegetable oil $0.04</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">2 Tbsp corn meal $0.03</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"ERSClear\"></div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSInstructions\">\n<div class=\"ERSInstructionsHeader ERSHeading\">Instructions</div>\n<ol>\n<li class=\"instruction\" itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">In a large bowl combine the flour, salt, yeast and water (I like to combine dry ingredients first then add water). Stir it until it forms a sticky ball. Loosely cover and let sit at room temperature for 14-18 hrs.</li>\n<li class=\"instruction\" itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">After fermentation, the dough should be wet, sticky, very bubbly and fluffy. Turn the dough over onto itself a few times until it is a slightly smaller and compact. Prepare a work surface by placing a sheet of plastic wrap on a wet countertop (this \u201cglues\u201d it into place) and sprinkling it with flour.</li>\n<li class=\"instruction\" itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Turn the sticky ball of dough out onto the flour covered plastic wrap. Sprinkle a little flour on top of the dough ball. Carefully stretch and shape the dough into a large rectangle. Prepare a baking sheet by smearing 1 Tbsp of vegetable oil over the surface and then sprinkling with corn meal. Pick the plastic wrap up and roll the rectangle of dough onto the prepared sheet. Reshape if necessary.</li>\n<li class=\"instruction\" itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Let the loaf rise for two hours (it will rise out rather than up). Preheat the oven to 425 degrees and bake the loaf for 25-30 minutes or until it is golden brown. Let the bread cool on a wire rack before slicing.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"ERSClear\"></div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"endeasyrecipe\" title=\"style002a\" style=\"display: none\">3.2.2124</div>\n</p></div>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h2><b>Step By Step Photos</b></h2>\n<p><img alt=\"dry bread ingredients\" src=\"http://lh5.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeMWg7AMI/AAAAAAAACR4/gWoRRHDkhas/s640/1%20dry%20ingredients.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><i>In a large bowl (or stock pot in my case) mix together the flour, salt and yeast.</i></p>\n<p><img alt=\"add water to dough\" src=\"http://lh4.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeMsOpvQI/AAAAAAAACR8/YF0b64Iytm0/s640/2%20wet%20dough.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><i>Pour in the water and stir it up until it&#8217;s a big sticky ball of dough.</i></p>\n<p><img alt=\"big fluffy fermented dough\" src=\"http://lh3.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeM1-bJvI/AAAAAAAACSA/ytwGdOU_QYE/s640/3%20fermentded%20dough.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><i>Let the mixture sit at room temperature for 14-18 hours, during which time it will get big, fluffy and full of bubbles.</i></p>\n<p><img alt=\"turn dough\" src=\"http://lh3.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeM4CneII/AAAAAAAACSE/SF1VffgfbSw/s640/4%20fermented%20dough%202.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><i>Turn the dough over on itself a few times to deflate. Coating your spatula with non-stick spray will keep it from sticking.</i></p>\n<p><img alt=\"turn out dough\" src=\"http://lh4.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeM7S8t9I/AAAAAAAACSI/TH9_sBsFGqw/s640/5%20dump%20dough.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><i>Place a sheet of plastic wrap on a wet counter top to anchor it down. Sprinkle the plastic wrap with flour and turn the dough out on top of it. Sprinkle a little flour on top of the dough so your hands don&#8217;t stick.</i></p>\n<p><img alt=\"shape dough\" src=\"http://lh5.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeVDWUbLI/AAAAAAAACSM/nkHoMjkluZU/s640/6%20shaped%20loaf.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><i>Gently shape the dough into a long rectangle (don&#8217;t make it longer than your baking sheet).</i></p>\n<p><img alt=\"risen loaf\" src=\"http://lh4.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeVGX3cXI/AAAAAAAACSQ/LKEcKjNYtas/s640/7%20risen%20loaf.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><i>Pick up the plastic wrap and roll the dough onto a baking sheet prepped with vegetable oil and corn meal. Let the dough rise for two hours. It will rise out rather than up like most breads (picture = after 2 hrs of rising).</i></p>\n<p><img alt=\"baked ciabatta\" src=\"http://lh6.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeVXRQjkI/AAAAAAAACSU/K_SJxUfiDuY/s640/8%20baked%20loaf.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><i>Bake the bread at 425 degrees for about 30 minutes or until the crust is medium brown. Let it cool before slicing.</i></p>\n<p><img alt=\"crust close up\" src=\"http://lh5.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeVahXNPI/AAAAAAAACSY/XeTfqIbOY6U/s640/9%20baked%20loaf.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"><i>It&#8217;s pretty.</i></p>\n<p><img alt=\"Ciabatta Sandwich\" src=\"http://lh4.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgeVp5V84I/AAAAAAAACSc/bkyqEjIAIfs/s640/Ciabatta%20sandwich.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"></p>\n<p>This bread is PERFECT for sandwiches. Light and fluffy inside with a good crust. YES!</p>\n<p>Oh, my other favorite thing about this bread is that <b>it only uses 1/4 tsp of yeast &#8211; TOTAL.</b> Now I can make great bread every week and my yeast will last four times as long.</p>\n\n<div class=\"nr_related_placeholder\" data-permalink=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/12/no-knead-ciabatta/\" data-title=\"no-knead ciabatta\"></div><div style=\"min-height:33px;\" class=\"really_simple_share really_simple_share_button robots-nocontent snap_nopreview\"><div class=\"really_simple_share_facebook_like\" style=\"width:90px;\"><iframe src=\"//www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.budgetbytes.com%2F2010%2F12%2Fno-knead-ciabatta%2F&amp;send=false&amp;layout=button_count&amp;width=90&amp;show_faces=false&amp;action=like&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=27&amp;locale=en_US\" \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tscrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:none; overflow:hidden; width:90px; height:27px;\" allowTransparency=\"true\"></iframe></div><div class=\"really_simple_share_twitter\" style=\"width:90px;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/share\" class=\"twitter-share-button\" data-count=\"horizontal\"  data-text=\"no-knead ciabatta\" data-url=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/12/no-knead-ciabatta/\"  data-via=\"\"   ></a></div><div class=\"really_simple_share_google1\" style=\"width:80px;\"><div class=\"g-plusone\" data-size=\"medium\" data-href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/12/no-knead-ciabatta/\" ></div></div><div class=\"really_simple_share_pinterest\" style=\"width:90px;\"><a data-pin-config=\"beside\" href=\"https://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/\" da