pare a baking sheet by smearing 1 Tbsp of vegetable oil over the surface and then sprinkling with corn meal. Pick the plastic wrap up and roll the rectangle of dough onto the prepared sheet. Reshape if necessary.", "Let the loaf rise for two hours (it will rise out rather than up). Preheat the oven to 425 degrees and bake the loaf for 25-30 minutes or until it is golden brown. Let the bread cool on a wire rack before slicing."], "images": [{"url": "http://lh6.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TPgedQJEBQI/AAAAAAAACSk/BioUeutIG6s/s640/Ciabatta%20sliced%20buttered.jpg", "path": "full/2af4e310b2674e1d2451601b7b48971c2c550005.jpg", "checksum": "623b88e9412eb4107996b5e2e54e8fde"}], "link": "http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/12/no-knead-ciabatta/", "recipe_cook_time": ["PT30M"], "recipe_yield": ["6"]}